res-grp     = acr-demo-rg
acr         = acrdemoijs
acr-repo    = aci-tutorial-app
localServer = acrdemoijs.azurecr.io 

1. Create and azure container 

az container create --resource-group acr-demo-rg --name aci-tutorial-app --image acrdemoijs.azurecr.io/aci-tutorial-app:v1
 --cpu 1 --memory 1 
 --registry-login-server acrdemoijs.azurecr.io
 --registry-username <service-principal-ID> --registry-password <service-principal-password> 
 --dns-name-label acr-demo-ijs --ports 80

 Both <service-principal-ID> & <service-principal-password>  can be found by running

* update to admin enabled 

az acr update -n acrdemoijs --admin-enabled true

* then 

az acr credential show -n acrdemoijs -o table

USERNAME    PASSWORD                          PASSWORD2
----------  --------------------------------  --------------------------------
acrdemoijs  XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX  xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

the 
<service-principal-ID> = acrdemoijs
<service-principal-password> = ENTER the PASSWORD

2. Check the status of the deployment with 

az container show --resource-group acr-demo-rg --name aci-tutorial-app --query ipAddress.fqdn

"acr-demo-ijs.uksouth.azurecontainer.io"

if you brpwse top http://acr-demo-ijs.uksouth.azurecontainer.io/

you'll see 

Hello World
Version: 9.11.2
